-- Argentina’s Banco Macro Reports Profit Rises 26% to $73 Million
-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 2012-05-11T15:55:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-11/argentina-s-banco-macro-reports-profit-rises-26-to-73-million.html
Banco Macro SA (BMA) , the nation’s largest
lender by market share, said first-quarter profit increased 26
percent from a year earlier to 324 million pesos ($73 million).  Total deposits increased 12 percent from the previous
quarter to 32.7 billion pesos, or 81 percent of total
liabilities, Banco Macro said today in a statement filed to
regulators.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in Buenos Aires at 
